	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>You guys are realy nice.&nbsp;&nbsp;I seriously wouldn't mind meeting you in RL.  This is the guy that just lost it the other day (about elves).  No one seriously flamed me.  You all used intellect to make good points even after I lost my grasp of reason and just ranted.  I applaud you.  Just wanted to say, I didn't mean in EQ that elves shouldn't be paladins.  It's fine.  Can you see what I mean about Elves being intellegent, ie. casters, that logic thread?  Now, I shot a hole in that logic a second ago (in my head).  There are different elves as there are different humans.  I'm basically saying (if EQ were in fact RL) that if I were off adventuring, I'd sure as hell take a High Elf Paladin, that went thru his 200+ years working out and getting great equipment, over a puny little 30+ year old human that never worked out and happened to find a set of rusty plate armor.<br><br>So, first...apologies for the rant :)<br>Second...thanks for taking it easy on me :)<br>Third, will someone find that 15th level SK and PK him for 32K please?...I've got 100pp for the one who does it :) (j/k of course..he's not worth that much)</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
